text: April unemployment rates ranged from 1.9% in SD to 5.4% in NV.
Between Q4 2021 and Q4 2022, house prices increased at least 10% in 15 states.
Real GDP growth between Q4 2021 and Q4 2022 ranged from -3.3% in NH to 4.4% in TX.
April average private weekly earnings in states ranged from MS’ $870 to MA’s $1,390.
Leisure and hospitality jobs in April 2023 were above April 2019 levels in 22 states.
Kansas saw its highest real manufacturing GDP level since 2005 in Q4 2022.
AZ, MD, and eight others saw historic lows in unemployment in April 2023.
Real retail GDP in Q4 2022 was higher than in Q4 2021 in 37 states.
Manufacturing jobs in April 2023 were above April 2019 levels in 29 states.
CA’s 2.3 percent year-over-year house price growth in Q4 2022 was its lowest in a decade.
State and local public education jobs in April 2023 were above 2019 levels in only 10 states.
